.TH GIT-RESOLVE-BASE 1 "2026-06-13" "git-tools" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
git-resolve-base \- print the inferred branch point of the current branch
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B git resolve-base
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B git resolve-base
resolves the branch point that the current branch diverged from and prints it.
The base ref is inferred in order: the configured upstream, a remote default
branch
.RB ( origin/HEAD
and friends), then a local default branch
.RB ( main ,
.BR master ,
or
.BR trunk ).
.PP
By default the merge-base commit (the branch point) is printed. Other git-tools
commands compose this command so base detection stays defined in one place.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-ref
Print the resolved base ref instead of the merge-base commit.
.TP
.B \-\-short
Abbreviate the merge-base commit id. Cannot be combined with
.BR \-\-ref .
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show help.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Base resolved and printed.
.TP
.B 2
Usage error, not in a repository, or base could not be determined.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR git-absorb-and-rebase (1),
.BR git-repo-state (1),
.BR git-merge-base (1)
